# Reloadux Project Conventions

## Component Reuse — Always Check Before Creating

Before writing ANY new UI pattern, check `src/components/ui/` for existing components etc:

- `SectionTag` — `[ TAG TEXT ]` labels. Always use `<SectionTag text="TAG" />` with ALL CAPS text. Use `variant="dark"` on dark backgrounds.
- `FlairButton` — Stroke button with hover fill animation + arrow. Sizes: `sm` (header), `md` (default), `lg` (hero/CTA). Variants: `light` (default, for dark bg), `dark` (for light bg). Use instead of custom link buttons.
- `Button` — Basic primary/outline button for forms.
- `ScrollReveal` — Fade-in-up animation triggered by intersection observer. Wrap any element for scroll-triggered entrance.
- `StatCounter` — Animated number counter for stat sections.
- `FAQItem` — Accordion item for FAQ sections.
- `BlogCard` — Blog post card with image, meta, and title.
- `CarouselDots` — Dot indicators for carousels. Props: `count`, `active`, `onDot`, `direction`.
- `VideoOverlay` — Full-screen video overlay with close button. Props: `videoUrl`, `onClose`.
- `ArrowNav` — Circular prev/next arrow buttons for carousels. Props: `onPrev`, `onNext`, `size`.

Never hardcode `[ TEXT ]` brackets in JSX — always use `SectionTag`.
Never duplicate the flair button markup — always use `FlairButton`.
Never build custom carousel nav — use `ArrowNav` and `CarouselDots`.

## Design Tokens — Use CSS Variables, Not Hardcoded Values

```css
/* BAD */
color: #090909;
font-family: "Manrope", sans-serif;
background: #D9D9D9;

/* GOOD */
color: var(--color-night);
font-family: var(--font-primary);
background: var(--color-smoke);
```

Key token mappings:
- `#090909` → `var(--color-night)` or `var(--bg-dark)`
- `#D9D9D9` → `var(--color-smoke)`
- `#D1D1D1` → `var(--color-grey-200)`
- `#A5A9AC` → `var(--color-grey-400)` or `var(--grey)` (footer grey)
- `#C3C3C3` → `var(--color-grey-300)` (blog meta grey)
- `#333333` → `var(--color-grey-700)` (dark bg borders)
- `#000000` → `var(--color-black)`
- `#FFFFFF` → `var(--color-white)`
- `#9662FF` → `var(--color-purple-500)` or `var(--purple)`
- `#A401B7` → `var(--color-purple-900)` or `var(--magenta)`
- `"Manrope"` → `var(--font-primary)`
- `"Libre Baskerville"` → `var(--font-serif)`
- `"Lexend"` → `var(--font-accent)`

Font usage rules:
- Manrope (`--font-primary`): all body/headings/nav/buttons
- Libre Baskerville (`--font-serif`): author names and section tag serif accents only
- Lexend (`--font-accent`): counter numbers only

## Section Headings — Consistent Pattern

ALL section headings (h2) must follow this exact pattern:

```css
font-family: var(--font-primary);  /* Manrope */
font-size: 48px;
font-weight: 400;
line-height: 1.35;
```

- On dark backgrounds: `color: var(--text-primary)` or `var(--color-white)`
- On light/smoke backgrounds: `color: var(--color-black)`
- Never use `--font-serif` (Libre Baskerville) or `--font-heading` for section headings
- Never use bold (700) for section headings — always 400

## Layout — 1280px Content Width

All sections follow this container pattern:
- Outer wrapper: full width, `padding-inline: var(--page-padding)` (80px)
- Inner content: `max-width: var(--content-width)` (1440px), `margin: 0 auto`
- Effective content area: 1280px (1440 - 80 - 80)

The header follows the same approach for alignment.

## Content Architecture — Strapi-First with JSON Fallback

- All content fetching goes through `src/lib/content.ts`
- It tries Strapi first, falls back to local JSON files in `content/pages/`
- Media URLs from Strapi use `getStrapiMediaUrl()` from `src/lib/media.ts`
- Never fetch Strapi directly from components — always use the content layer

## WordPress Reference

The design source of truth is `reloadux.com` (WordPress/Elementor). When implementing or fixing sections, compare against the live WP site for typography, spacing, colors, and interactions.
